org.lightsleep.entity

Annotation Type InsertProperty


  • @Documented
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Repeatable(value=InsertProperties.class)
 @Target(value=TYPE)
public @interface InsertProperty
    Indicates an expression instead of the value of the field defined in superclass used in INSERT SQL.

    This annotation is used to specify for fields defined in superclass. The specified contents also affects subclasses, but specifications in the subclass takes precedence. If you specify expression="", the specification in the superclass is canceled.

    Java Example
      @InsertProperty(property="createdTime", expression="CURRENT_TIMESTAMP")
  @InsertProperty(property="updatedTime", expression="CURRENT_TIMESTAMP")
   public class Person extends PersonBase {
    Groovy Example
      @InsertProperties([
    @InsertProperty(property='createdTime', expression='CURRENT_TIMESTAMP'),
    @InsertProperty(property='updatedTime', expression='CURRENT_TIMESTAMP')
  ])
  public class Person extends PersonBase {
    Generated SQL
     INSERT INTO ... (..., createdTime, updatedTime) VALUES (..., CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP)
    Since:
    1.3.0
    Author:
    Masato Kokubo
    See Also:
    Insert, InsertProperties
